<br>
Well once you finish your defensive AA's you're going to be left with a bunch of lackluster offensive aa's to train anyway, so no reason not to have them at least prove effective for the points spent. <br>
<br>
Personally I already have alot of defensive abilities trained. Aside from the obvious DPS benefits one of my goals for getting my offensives done now asap was for better aggro management durring speedy trashmob clearing sessions in places like Tactics, Saryrns Tower, HoHB, Bertoxx Ring, Mez Breaking etc etc etc where the trash mobs are doing extrordinary damage per round. <br>
<br>
In most of these places we don't have the time nor do we want to take the time per kill just to stand around letting a warrior beat on it to gain sufficient aggro before calling everyone else in. What alot of guilds are doing right now is replacing warriors all together in these situations and getting a Paladin/SK to do all the aggro mgmt and tanking due to the fact they are flat out better at getting aggro faster and holding it more reliably than equally equipped warriors due to the nature of thier spells.<br>
<br>
Personally I just wanted an edge in the aggro control department to help me get and keep aggro durring these marathon trash clearing sessions. Boss Mob control is not an issue for me, since boss mobs are ussually properly respected by the players as something they should be paying attention to thier aggro for. <br>
<br>
I'm tired of being forced to sit on the side falling asleep durring a 4 hour snoozefest hitting auto-attack once every couple of minutes while a multi-functional class gets to play the ONLY role I have to offer the raid. These offensive AA's, to me, were my way of helping to overcome some of our shortcommings in the instant aggro and aggro management dept to help put myself back into the role I've played this character 3 years to fill.<br>
<br>
If I wanted to stand off to the side while another class did all the tanking durring these sessions I'd have made a rogue, at least I'd have sufficient dps to offer for my other shortcommins. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160002"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnimwit>Gnimwit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimflag.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/14/02 11:26:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/02 7:10:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2624.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior Offensive AA: Not all they could be, letdown</span><hr size=1> Nope, your hit rate can be 1% or 100%, TM3 will still increase your DPS by the exact same %.  This is because everyone use special defense before the hit/miss check (e.g. you will never 'miss' an enrage mob, and likewise a mob will never 'miss' a player using Nimble/WS/Furious.  Special skills are used before the hit/miss check is even computed)<br>
<br>
Let's use the example above, mob uses special defenses 10% of the time, you pierce through special defense 50% of the time.<br>
<br>
Without TM3, 90% of your swing actually goes to the hit/miss check, and 10% gets negated to nothingness.  <br>
<br>
With TM3, 95% of your swing gets to make hit/miss check, and 5% swings get negated to nothingness.  <br>
<br>
Old DPS is 90% X your hit rate<br>
New DPS is 95% X your hit rate<br>
<br>
Since your hit rate doesn't change, the ratio of your new DPS to old DPS is exactly 95/90, which is about a gain of 5.5% DPS.  <br>
<br>
Of course, we don't exactly how much TM3 pierces through defenses but 50% seems like a good estimate.  Note that just because it pierces 50% doesn't mean you'll hit a mob on enrage 50% because roughly half of your hits will be a miss even after you get through the riposte.  Although I obviously don't have an extensive log of fight against riposte, 1 out of 4 connect through enrage seems about right.<br>
<br>
I did the numbers for most using special skills 15% of the time and it turns out you get roughly 8% DPS increase.  Basically the more often a mob can use special defenses, the bigger the gains from Tactical Mastery, and since warriors don't always have the option of hitting a mob from behind, this DPS is considerable, especially for xp groups where we're almost always in the front.<br>
<br>
To put an extreme example, you get an infinite % improvement in DPS versus an enraged mob, from 0 before to whatever that actually hurt a mob through enrage.<br>
<br>
So assuming these numbers, 9 AAs for 5.5% DPS increase in xp situation isn't too bad, at least in line with most of the offensive AAs (in fact, I'm pretty sure Flurry is less than this).  The defensive part reminds unverified to this date as we only have enrage logs to test the defensive part, and it's not clear enrage works the same as regular riposte. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnimwit>Gnimwit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/02 7:42:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2624.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimp.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior Offensive AA: Not all they could be, letdown</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Nope, your hit rate can .....<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
