Roughly same DPS increase as Ambidextery and same AA cost, but only working from the front. Does not reduce damage taken from ripostes at all. [EDIT: This is theoretical assuming 50% successrate on TM..]<br>
<br>
So if you dont have ambidextery and use dualwield, ambidextery is still the better buy, as it is not restricted to frontal attack only. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/16/02 6:22:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 2:21:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2624.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior Offensive AA: Not all they could be, letdown</span><hr size=1> I've posted on another thread, but there is no definitive parse prove TM doesn't work against normal riposte yet.  So far the only proof is that it doesn't work against enrage, but not on normal ripostes (enrage isn't the same as normal riposte).  <br>
<br>
Let's assume for a moment TM actually works but only on regular ripostes.  We still can't tell.  Why?  Instead of:<br>
<br>
X hit you (or miss)<br>
You try to hit X but X Riposte<br>
<br>
You'd get:<br>
<br>
You try to hit X but miss <br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
You hit X for Y<br>
<br>
However, the two examples where it works is completely indistinqishable from a normal hit or a normal miss because you no longer see the riposte part (assuming it works).  In fact, the only thing you can observe from a log is where TM failed, i.e.<br>
<br>
X hits you for Y (or miss)<br>
You hit X for Y (or miss, but not riposte)<br>
<br>
since those two circumstances can never happen normally (assuming X isn't attacking you).  <br>
<br>
Mind you, no evidence to prove it doesn't work doesn't mean it works, but we still don't have conclusive proof that it doesn't work against normal ripostes.  I'm going to keep my hopes up until proven otherwise. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A> at: 12/16/02 2:24:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnimwit>Gnimwit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 2:43:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2624.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimp.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior Offensive AA: Not all they could be, letdown</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>However, the two examples where it works is completely indistinqishable from a normal hit or a normal miss because you no longer see the riposte part (assuming it works). In fact, the only thing you can observe from a log is where TM failed, i.e.<br>
